302
00:52:27,416 --> 00:52:30,510
But the City of Vienna
never received that money.

303
00:52:30,986 --> 00:52:33,750
Instead, the money was transferred...

304
00:52:33,889 --> 00:52:37,086
...to banks in England and elsewhere.

305
00:52:37,893 --> 00:52:39,292
They took the money...

306
00:52:39,428 --> 00:52:44,730
...and for years to come will pay...

307
00:52:44,866 --> 00:52:50,270
...periodic leasing instalments
to the American investor...

308
00:52:50,405 --> 00:52:53,772
...so that the City of Vienna
has the right...

309
00:52:53,909 --> 00:52:55,342
...to use the trams.

310
00:52:56,745 --> 00:52:58,178
<i>Can you imagine that?</i>

311
00:53:12,394 --> 00:53:16,353
<i>The state is the community
of all people living in that state.</i>

312
00:53:16,498 --> 00:53:18,295
<i>We are the state.</i>

313
00:53:18,600 --> 00:53:21,296
<i>This applies at least
to a democracy.</i>

314
00:53:21,536 --> 00:53:24,198
<i>In order to organize
a functioning society...</i>

315
00:53:24,639 --> 00:53:26,163
<i>...the state needs public goods...</i>

316
00:53:26,675 --> 00:53:28,973
<i>Schools, universities...</i>

317
00:53:29,111 --> 00:53:32,603
<i>...public transport, etc.</i>

318
00:53:33,115 --> 00:53:35,481
<i>In this context,
it is interesting to see...</i>

319
00:53:35,617 --> 00:53:39,644
<i>...what is going on
with privatization.</i>

320
00:53:40,088 --> 00:53:43,319
<i>" Privatization" originates
from the Latin word "privare"</i>

321
00:53:43,458 --> 00:53:45,085
...which means "to deprive".

322
00:53:47,028 --> 00:53:49,189
<i>In the process
of privatization...</i>

323
00:53:49,498 --> 00:53:51,295
...public goods
are bought...

324
00:53:52,601 --> 00:53:55,263
...by private investors.

325
00:53:55,904 --> 00:53:59,135
Sometimes they even receive them
as a present.

326
00:53:59,641 --> 00:54:02,075
This is nothing else...

327
00:54:02,210 --> 00:54:05,702
...than depriving society
of public goods.

328
00:54:06,314 --> 00:54:08,544
You could sum it up as follows:

329
00:54:08,683 --> 00:54:11,584
Society is deprived of a certain good...

330
00:54:11,720 --> 00:54:17,158
...that the private investor
is interested in...

331
00:54:17,292 --> 00:54:19,317
...for reasons of profit.

332
00:54:38,113 --> 00:54:42,447
<i>This strange system called
"cross-border-leasing"</i>

333
00:54:42,584 --> 00:54:44,449
<i>...has been widely applied...</i>

334
00:54:44,586 --> 00:54:48,852
<i>...not only in the case
of the viennese trams.</i>

335
00:54:49,157 --> 00:54:52,957
The Austrian Federal Railways...

336
00:54:53,094 --> 00:54:57,690
...sold their trains
to American investors.

337
00:54:59,167 --> 00:55:03,365
The City of Innsbruck
sold its public utilities.

338
00:55:05,273 --> 00:55:08,902
<i>Since we live in the era
of globalization...</i>

339
00:55:09,044 --> 00:55:11,774
...this didn't only take place in Austria...

340
00:55:11,913 --> 00:55:15,405
...but also in Germany, the Netherlands
